{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9dae1c2-b7cf-4a21-acb7-c0bc69ec44ea","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\nMSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible project file — no explicit package references needed:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it. `MSTest.Sdk` bundles the test runner, framework, and analyzers automatically.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a `[assembly:]` attribute in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs` (or any `.cs` file):\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\n- **`MethodLevel`** — runs individual test methods in parallel (maximum parallelism).\n- **`ClassLevel`** — runs test classes in parallel, but methods within a class run sequentially.\n\nPick `MethodLevel` unless you have shared per-class state.\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Insert_Record()\n    {\n        // runs sequentially, never overlaps with other [DoNotParallelize] tests\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Should_Read_Record()\n    {\n        // also sequential\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**How it works:** All `[DoNotParallelize]` tests run on a single thread *after* the parallelized tests complete. This guarantees no concurrent database access.\n\n### Quick summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project | `Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\"` — no PackageReferences |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class or method |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6068b10d-0256-4836-b645-9185ce68d084","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking for general MSTest setup guidance. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk.","outputTokens":577,"requestId":"E45B:18853A:3F0BB40:4538DBA:6A02FC0E"},"id":"0f1acd29-f07f-4572-86fd-df1e180278b8","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:08:27.058Z","parentId":"80652a96-8dfe-4ed9-8bc3-e795bdbac3b8"}
